      • $

        public static <K,V,M extends java.util.Map<K,V>> M $(M map,
                                                     JSONLike<K,V> entries)
        put entries into the given map.
        usually used when initializing a map.
        however you can also put entries into already existed maps.
        Parameters:
        map - the map to put entries into
        entries - entries to put, in the form of a JSONLike object.
        a JSONLike object can be created with map(Object, Object)
        and can put in entries using JSONLike.$(Object, Object)
        e.g. 
                        map("cass", 1995).$("john", 1994).$("cassie", 1996)
        Returns:
        param map
        See Also:
        JSONLike, map(Object, Object)

      • join

        @SafeVarargs
public static <T> java.util.List<T> join(java.util.List<T>... toJoin)
        Join lists into one, the joined list's elements are in order of argument order and original lists' element order
        you cannot modify the returned joined list's size.
        in other words, the joined list doesn't support methods like add, remove, addAll, retainAll, removeAll...
